    "companyProfile": "Enterprise software platform serving revenue leaders, sellers, service operators, and admins through CRM, monetization, service, data, automation, and AI workflows.",
    "operatingModel": "Revenue teams own pipeline and monetization loops. Service teams own assisted and digital service operations. Platform teams own data, identity, automation, AI, and integration foundations shared across every customer workflow.",
    "designPrinciples": [
      "Keep account and opportunity workflows close to manager inspection because customers judge them as one operating loop.",
      "Keep configuration, pricing, quote, and billing logic tightly connected because revenue friction appears at the handoff boundaries.",
      "Keep self-service, knowledge, and AI guidance together because digital containment only works when those layers reinforce each other.",
      "Keep trusted data, identity, and automation governance together because AI adoption depends on the combined trust posture."
    ],
    "staffingPrinciple": "Prefer teams of roughly 6-9 FTE with clear customer and brick ownership.",
    "groupingPrinciple": "Use top-level groups for revenue acquisition, monetization, service operations, and platform foundations.",
    "groupLeadershipPrinciple": "Use cross-group leadership around forecast trust, quote-to-cash speed, service deflection quality, and trusted AI adoption."
